  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Assistant / Chef de Partie (Pastry)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Calling All Pastry Chefs 🍰Lady M is Hiring!</strong> 👩‍🍳</p><p>Love pastries and take pride in your craft? If you’re passionate, hands-on, and ready to grow with us—we’d love to meet you!</p><p><strong>Role Summary</strong><br /><br />Lady M is urgently looking for passionate and motivated <strong>Assistant / Chef de Partie (Pastry)</strong> to support daily pastry production and maintain high standards of quality, consistency, and hygiene in our kitchen operations.<br /><br /><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><p>Assist in the preparation and production of pastries, desserts, cakes, and crêpes according to established recipes and standards</p></li><li><p>Carry out daily mise en place and basic baking tasks</p></li><li><p>Ensure product quality, portion control, and consistency</p></li><li><p>Maintain cleanliness and organisation of workstations in accordance with food hygiene and safety regulations</p></li><li><p>Follow SOPs, food safety guidelines, and kitchen policies</p></li><li><p>Support inventory handling and minimise wastage</p></li><li><p>Work closely with senior chefs to ensure smooth kitchen operations</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><p>Applicants must be legally authorised to work in Singapore without the need for employer sponsorship.</p><ul><li><p>Relevant pastry or bakery experience preferred</p></li><li><p>Willingness to learn and take instruction in a production kitchen</p></li><li><p>Ability to work in a fast-paced environment</p></li><li><p>Team player with a positive attitude</p></li><li><p><strong>Able to start immediately or on short notice preferred</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Experience in crêpe making and/or mille crêpes baking will be an advantage</strong></p></li></ul><h3><strong>Working Conditions</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Willing to work shifts, weekends, and public holidays</p></li><li><p>Physically fit to stand for long hours</p></li></ul>",
